metadata.name: NEBULAE #67
metadata.description:
NEBULAE invites you to deep space exploration to search for rare nebulas. As a space explorer you will most likely encounter an NGC, the common nebula type, but on your travels there is an possibility you will witness the powerful creative forces of the universe.. or discover something even more magical.

This project was created with randomly generated Embergen particle simulations combined with cables.gl background setup. I want to deeply thank Murat Atimtay for all the help with this first generative mint and VerticalCryptoArt & somaticbits for their helpful resources.


[e] save as png

I hope this series sparks your imagination and love for color as it did for me.

- Walt

metadata.name: Tumble Down Light Factory #106
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden â€œtemplateâ€ canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden â€˜templateâ€™ image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.name: Mythologic #734
metadata.description:
"Mythologic" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022.

Mythologic is a project derived from cloud series, Cloud Atlas and Requiem: Cloud on fxhash. In the series, lines and circles are used in an organics movement like Cloud Hands, which is a move of Tai Chi. Practitioners move their hands slowly and smoothly, make circles and rotate with extreme concentrating. In Chinese we said â€œfloating clouds and flowing waterâ€ to describe calligraphersâ€™ freely flowing style of writing. Chi is a very important for oriental artists, and for genart as well. In the series, lines and circles start from one position to another, and develop with organic rotations and movements, like practicing Tai Chi on the canvas. 

Mythologic was inspired from â€œClassic of Mountains and Seasâ€, also known as Shan Hai Jing, is a Chinese classic text and a compilation of mythic geography and beasts. 

â€œThere is a beast that looks like a fox with nine tails.â€ 
â€œHuangbei: it is a beetle with meat like a tadpole, but with a head and a tailâ€ 
â€œThe beast has the body of a fish but the wings of a birdâ€ 

There are many incredible creatures in the text which describe the oriental fantasy. The idea of Mythologic is to present an illustrated handbook with random generated paintings, each one is like a framed badge, to memorize the glorious age. It uses the "cloud hands" technique in every parts of this piece, the center, the circle and the frame. They are all the same algorithm but perform variety with different density and components. Gold, Silver, Copper, Jade and Ruby colors as noble symbol of treasure in Chinese culture. 

This project use p5js. 

Press 'S' to save pictures.

Thanks to the support of Yi-Wen Lin in this project.

metadata.name: Elasticity #177
metadata.description:
Elasticity is a collection that explores the ambiguity of discrete continuity in architecture.

Elasticity is a tectonic, generative system that combines simple, discrete parts into an elastic relationship between part and whole, creating a discrete and continuous elastic form. A form that celebrates the continuity of digital variation while respecting a discrete approach to a digital whole.

It is a generative follow-up to the project CM.CollabWood, where the same parts were embedded in a real-time participatory architectural environment, where clusters of parts were placed by participants in real-time in collective design sessions to create tangible collective open forms.

___________________________________________________
Controls:
â€¢ 'P' pause/play animation
â€¢ 'B' monochrome mode (wait a bit for recalculation)

Resize Canvas in live/open mode:
(press once and wait for recalculation!)
â€¢ 'DoubleClick' go Fullscreen
â€¢ '1' square 1024x1024
â€¢ '2' square 2048x2048
â€¢ '3' square 3072x3072
â€¢ '4' square 4096x4096 (might not work on all laptops)
â€¢ '5' landscape 4000x3000
â€¢ '6' portrait 3000x4000
â€¢ '7' fullHD 1920x1080
â€¢ '8' UHD 3840 x 2160
â€¢ '9' square small(for sharing a gif on twitter) 512x512
â€¢ '0' flex. adapt to current window size

Save & Export in live/open mode:
â€¢ 's' save a .png of in current resolution
â€¢ 'g' save a seamless loop .gif in current resolution
(press the key and wait for export, might take some time, consider with higher resolutions files get pretty big)

Steps to save a gif/png :
â€¢ go in live/open mode (wait)
â€¢ resize canvas to your desired resolution (wait)
â€¢ press s or g and wait for recalculation & download to finish
â€¢ enjoy elasticity :)
___________________________________________________


This token may not work on mobile(!), but it allows exporting .png and .gif (see controls) to enjoy elasticity on different displays or mobile. Tested on Mozilla, Chrome, Safari. Created with P5js & p5.createLoop

metadata.name: Glomularus #166
metadata.description:
Glomularus is an exploration in generative, artificial life forms. The project is an extension of my Protobyte series, begun in 2004.

Driven by Verlet icosahedra and responsive tendrils, Glomulari live in a spherical virtual ecosystem (V-eco) enhanced through user interaction.

Interaction:

Mouse/Trackpad:
  drag -> camera rotation
  drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
  scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
  1-9: add acceleration
  -, +: reduce | increase V-eco sphere radius
  f, g: reduce | increase fog
  p: screen capture

Tip:
To decrease creature acceleration, reduce V-eco sphere radius

Note:
Please post your favorite Glomularus screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

metadata.name: Annihilate This Week #210
metadata.description:
This is a companion piece to "Saturday Night's Alright (For Fighting)" (project #14045). Same algorithm of the previous one, only slightly modified, the main difference is that here the daily variations are all mixed up together and the output doesn't change based on the current day.

This is intended to be a gift for all collectors and the community of fx(hash) that showed so much support for the "Saturday" project, really beyond my expectations.

50% of the royalties goes to the minter, do with the piece whatever you'd like, hold it, sell or trade it, or even burn it if you really don't like it :)

Thank you!

----

Made with p5.js
